$ /lib

`/lib` is the directory for the *essential shared shared libraries and kernel modules*: the libraries needed to boot the system up and
run executables in the root filesystem (that is: binaries in → Linux/fhs/lib[`/lib`] and → Linux/fhs/sbin/[`/sbin`].


sa:

  → Linux/fhs/usr/lib

  → development/dynamic-loader

  → https://refspecs.linuxfoundation.org/FHS_3.0/fhs/ch03s09.html
